Female
(
Paratype
UFRJ
1417). Carapace and endites light yellow, bearing a wide median brown stripe from eyes to fovea, with abundant black pigment, blackish sides and a lighter median patch (
Fig. 2A
). Carapace slightly tapering towards its anterior elevated part, but not as narrow as in male (
Fig. 2A
). Eyes, sternum and legs as in male (
Fig. 2A–B
). Chelicerae with brown paturon and reddish brown fangs (
Fig. 2B
). Abdomen conical (
Fig. 2A
), dorsum beige, with a pair of dark patches at each side of white cardiac area, a pair of black patches on middle third and a big black area on posterior third (
Fig. 2A
). Lateral part of abdomen covered by a black stripe (
Fig. 2B
). Venter beige, with a rectangular black patch just above spinnerets and a pair of black patches on opposite sides of epigynal area (
Fig. 2B
). Spinnerets and anal tubercle light brown. Epigynum oval, much wider than long, with large and protruding rounded lips, a short and small rounded scape, much lighter than surrounding areas (
Fig. 2C– D
), and a large and roundish notch, resembling an inverted water drop (
Fig. 2C
). Posterior plate much wider than high and slightly laterally depressed, covered by lips only at its edges (
Fig. 2D
). Total length: 4.58. Carapace: 2.00 long, 1.48 wide. Leg I: femur 1,53, patella 0.67, tibia 1.27, metatarsus 1.18 and tarsus 0.67. Patella + tibia II 1.63; III 1.26; IV 1.93.
